1""" 

2Multi-Spectral Distributions of the Colour Matching Functions 

3============================================================= 

4 

5Define the multi-spectral distributions of the colour matching functions. 

6 

7The colour matching functions data is in the form of a *dict* of 

8:class:`colour.colorimetry.MultiSpectralDistributions` classes as follows:: 

9 

10 {'name': MultiSpectralDistributions, 

11 ..., 

12 'name': MultiSpectralDistributions} 

13 

14The following colour matching functions are available: 

15 

16- Stockman & Sharpe 2 Degree Cone Fundamentals 

17- Stockman & Sharpe 10 Degree Cone Fundamentals 

18- Smith & Pokorny 1975 Normal Trichromats 

19- Wright & Guild 1931 2 Degree RGB CMFs 

20- Stiles & Burch 1955 2 Degree RGB CMFs 

21- Stiles & Burch 1959 10 Degree RGB CMFs 

22- CIE 1931 2 Degree Standard Observer 

23- CIE 1964 10 Degree Standard Observer 

24- CIE 2015 10 Degree Standard Observer 

25- CIE 2015 2 Degree Standard Observer 

26 

27Notes 

28----- 

29- *Stockman & Sharpe* *LMS* colour matching functions are provided at 1 nm 

30 interval. 

31- *Smith & Pokorny* normal trichromats colour matching functions are provided 

32 at 5 nm steps. 

33- *Wright & Guild* and *Stiles & Burch* *CIE RGB* colour matching functions 

34 are provided at 5 nm interval. 

35- *CIE* Standard Observers *XYZ* colour matching functions are provided at 5 

36 nm interval. 

37 

38References 

39---------- 

40- :cite:`Broadbent2009a` : Broadbent, A. D. (2009). Calculation from the 

41 Original Experimental Data of the Cie 1931 RGB Standard Observer Spectral 

42 Chromaticity Co-Ordinates and Color Matching Functions. Québec, Canada: 

43 Département de Génie Chimique, …. Retrieved June 12, 2014, from 

44 http://www.cis.rit.edu/mcsl/research/1931.php 

45- :cite:`CVRLr` : CVRL. (n.d.). New CIE XYZ functions transformed from the 

46 CIE (2006) LMS functions. Retrieved February 24, 2014, from 

47 http://cvrl.ioo.ucl.ac.uk/ciexyzpr.htm 

48- :cite:`CVRLs` : CVRL. (n.d.). Older CIE Standards. Retrieved February 24, 

49 2014, from http://cvrl.ioo.ucl.ac.uk/cie.htm 

50- :cite:`CVRLt` : CVRL. (n.d.). Stiles & Burch individual 10-deg colour 

51 matching data. Retrieved February 24, 2014, from 

52 http://www.cvrl.org/stilesburch10_ind.htm 

53- :cite:`CVRLu` : Stockman, A., & Sharpe, L. T. (2000). Cone Fundamentals. 

54 Retrieved June 23, 2014, from http://www.cvrl.org/cones.htm 

55- :cite:`CVRLw` : CVRL. (n.d.). Stiles & Burch individual 2-deg colour 

56 matching data. Retrieved February 24, 2014, from 

57 http://www.cvrl.org/stilesburch2_ind.htm 

58- :cite:`Machado2010a` : Machado, Gustavo Mello. (2010). A model for 

59 simulation of color vision deficiency and a color contrast enhancement 

60 technique for dichromats. (pp. 1-94). 

61 http://www.lume.ufrgs.br/handle/10183/26950 

62"""
